The four police officers accused of murder in the shooting death of Amadou Diallo plan to testify in their own defense at their trial next month and are leaning toward choosing a trial by a judge instead of a jury, according to their lawyers.
An appellate court ordered the trial of the four officers accused of killing Amadou Diallo to be moved to Albany County, ruling on Thursday that a fair trial would be impossible in the Bronx because of ``the public clamor'' about the case.
